subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of genitalia.
Pygophore (
Figs. 10D
, 
17F
) compressed dorsoventrally, semicircular in ventral view, strongly concave at anterior margin of dorsum, elevated at center of venter, smooth on surface, irregularly punctate in middle part of dorsum. Paramere (
Fig. 18F
) expanded in middle part, curved inward in apical part; outer and inner margins covered with pubescence in middle part. Female terminalia (
Fig. 11D
) pentagonal in ventral view, covered with pubescence.

